<div id="review_3537103378" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3537103378" />
    <a title="Cinzia DuBois" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6341226-cinzia-dubois"><img alt="Cinzia DuBois" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1394151036p2/6341226.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3537103378?book_show_action=true">Sep 08, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cinzia DuBois" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cinzia DuBois" href="/user/show/6341226-cinzia-dubois">Cinzia DuBois</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781474602266" href="/book/show/29611286-the-witches">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3537103378" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3688032591682394036">DNF<br/><br/>I’m in agreement with other 2 star reviewers of this book. A lack of thesis and bizarrely scatty yet overly detailed, dry writing isn’t an enticing combination. I’ll have to find a better book about the Salem Witch trials. If you’re interested in reading a good book about witch-hunting, read Goodare’s ‘The European Witch-hunt’<br/><br/>I only gave it two stars to credit the author&apos;s extensive research. This may be a useful research reference book for someone writing a dissertation on the subject. Just </span>
  <span id="freeText3688032591682394036" style="display:none">DNF<br /><br />I’m in agreement with other 2 star reviewers of this book. A lack of thesis and bizarrely scatty yet overly detailed, dry writing isn’t an enticing combination. I’ll have to find a better book about the Salem Witch trials. If you’re interested in reading a good book about witch-hunting, read Goodare’s ‘The European Witch-hunt’<br /><br />I only gave it two stars to credit the author's extensive research. This may be a useful research reference book for someone writing a dissertation on the subject. Just don't expect to quote her in your dissertation. Not if you don't want your marker to fall asleep...</span>
